        <section class="future" id="futureplans">
            <h1>Future Plans</h1>
            <div class="firstgroup">
                <div>
                    <img src="../images/fish.png" alt="fish">
                    <h2>Fish Pond Project</h2>
                    <p>To promote diversification and improve nutrition in the community, the farm plans to establish a fish pond for aquaculture production. This project will not only provide a new source of protein for local families but also create opportunities for learning and income generation for villagers interested in fish farming. The goal is to make fish accessible, affordable, and sustainably produced within the community.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <img src="../images/slaughter house.jpg" alt="slaughter house">
                    <h2>Slaughter House Development</h2>
                    <p>As the farm’s livestock production grows, establishing a modern slaughterhouse will ensure that animals are processed humanely, hygienically, and in line with quality standards. This project will enable the farm to add value to its meat products, open up new markets, and provide safe, locally sourced meat to consumers. It will also create employment opportunities and reduce the need to rely on distant processing centers.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <img src="../images/maize flour.jpg" alt="maize flour">
                    <h2>Maize Milling Plant</h2>
                    <p>With maize being one of the farm’s major crops, plans are underway to set up a maize mill that will process grain into flour for local and regional markets. By milling maize on-site, the farm will be able to produce affordable, high-quality flour while supporting local food security. This project will also strengthen the local economy by sourcing raw materials and distributing products within the village and beyond.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="secondgroup">
                <div>
                    <img src="../images/animal feeds.jpg" alt="animal feeds">
                    <h2>Animal Feed Production</h2>
                    <p>To support livestock rearing both on the farm and in the wider community, the farm aims to develop its own animal feed production unit. Producing feeds locally will reduce costs, improve quality control, and ensure a consistent supply of nutritious feed for animals. Eventually, the farm intends to sell these feeds to other farmers at affordable prices — helping them improve productivity and sustainability.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <img src="../images/goats.jpg" alt="animal feeds">
                    <h2>Goat Rearing</h2>
                    <p>The farm plans to venture into goat rearing to diversify livestock production. Goats are hardy and adaptable, providing both milk and meat for local consumption. This project will boost income generation and serve as a model for sustainable livestock farming in the community.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <img src="../images/Packaged milk.jpg" alt="packaged milk">
                    <h2>Milk Packaging & Mala</h2>
                    <p>The farm also plans to begin packaging its own milk to maintain freshness, ensure quality, and reach a wider market. Additionally, there are plans to introduce Maziwa Mala (cultured sour milk), a traditional East African favorite known for its rich flavor and nutritional benefits. Through value addition, the farm hopes to increase profits, extend product shelf life, and strengthen its brand identity as a provider of fresh, wholesome dairy products.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

